130 And I answer: I believe in one God 131 alone and eternal, who moves all the sky, 132 not motion, with love and with desire;
133 and to such belief I have not yet proofs 134 physical and metaphysical, but from them 135 also the truth that from here rains
136 through Moses, through prophets and through psalms, 137 through the Gospel and through you who wrote 138 since the burning Spirit made you almi;
139 and I believe in three eternal persons, and these 140 I believe one essence so one and so threefold, 141 that suffers conjoint “am” and “are”.

